files.Summary: Used to decorate xUnit.net test assemblies to indicate per-assembly fixture data. An instance of the fixture data is initialized before any test in the assembly are run (including if it's implemented). After all the tests in the assembly have been run, it is cleaned up by calling if it's implemented, or it falls back to if that's implemented. Assembly fixtures must have a public parameterless constructor. To gain access to the fixture data from inside the test, a constructor argument should be added to the test class which exactly matches the fixture type.
